# Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your values:

```env
# Database
# For Supabase: https://supabase.com
# For Railway: https://railway.app
# Format: postgresql://user:password@host:port/database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/vlookup

# n8n Configuration
# For self-hosted: http://localhost:5678
# For n8n cloud: https://your-instance.n8n.cloud
NEXT_PUBLIC_N8N_URL=http://localhost:5678

# n8n API Key (if using n8n API directly)
# Get this from n8n Settings → API Keys
N8N_API_KEY=your-n8n-api-key-here

# API Security
# Use a strong random token for production
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
API_INTERNAL_TOKEN=demo-key-12345
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_KEY=demo-key-12345

# Optional: Email Configuration (for n8n)
# If using Gmail SMTP:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
# SMTP_FROM=noreply@vlookup.com

# Optional: Vercel Deployment
# VERCEL_URL is auto-set by Vercel
# For local development, leave empty
VERCEL_URL=
```

## Setup Guide

### 1. Database
```bash
# Option A: Supabase (Recommended)
# 1. Go to supabase.com → Create project
# 2. Copy PostgreSQL connection string
# 3. Paste into DATABASE_URL

# Option B: Railway
# 1. Go to railway.app → Create PostgreSQL
# 2. Copy connection string
# 3. Paste into DATABASE_URL

# Option C: Local PostgreSQL
brew install postgresql@15
brew services start postgresql@15
createdb vlookup
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://localhost/vlookup
```

### 2. n8n
```bash
# Self-hosted (Docker)
docker run -d -p 5678:5678 n8nio/n8n

# Or use n8n Cloud
# NEXT_PUBLIC_N8N_URL=https://your-instance.n8n.cloud

# Get API Key:
# 1. Log in to n8n
# 2. Settings → API Keys
# 3. Create new key
# 4. Paste into N8N_API_KEY
```

### 3. Security
```bash
# Generate secure token for API_INTERNAL_TOKEN
openssl rand -base64 32

# Example output: aB+xYz9kLmNoPqR1sTu2vWx3yZ4aBcD5eF=
# Copy this into API_INTERNAL_TOKEN and NEXT_PUBLIC_API_KEY
```

### 4. Deployment to Vercel
```bash
# Install Vercel CLI
npm i -g vercel

# Deploy
vercel

# Add environment variables
vercel env add DATABASE_URL
vercel env add N8N_API_KEY
vercel env add API_INTERNAL_TOKEN
vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_N8N_URL
vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_API_KEY

# Redeploy with env vars
vercel --prod
```

## Verification

```bash
# Test database connection
npm run db:push

# Test API locally
npm run dev
curl http://localhost:3000/api/clients

# Check n8n connection
curl $NEXT_PUBLIC_N8N_URL/api/v1/workflows
```

## Security Best Practices

- [ ] Never commit `.env.local` to git
- [ ] Use `.env.example` for public template
- [ ] Rotate API keys quarterly
- [ ] Use HTTPS in production
- [ ] Add rate limiting to API endpoints
- [ ] Validate all webhook payloads
- [ ] Log all API requests (avoid PII)
- [ ] Use database credentials from secrets manager
